  "text": "The M&M theory proposed by Modigliani and Miller [CITATION_1] shows that a firm's financial and operational decision are independent in a perfect capital market. However, Hite et al. [CITATION_2] point out that the market is always imperfect in real life, so a firm's financing and operational decisions will interact each other.",
